<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<a href="./amaurea">amaurea</a>: How about a more spectre-like version of the spectre subrace? Spectres are etheral creatures held together solely by their own will, and not by any physical substance. They should therefor have no hp (permanent max hp of 1), but have a permanent disruption shield, so they take damage with their sp. <p>
This means that a spectre can't heal with normal healing potions or healing spells, only with potions of mana and such. It also means that a spectre must be careful not to tire its mind too much (use too much sp), as this makes its 'body' more vulnerable. To compensate they should have a bit more sp than a normal char. 
</p>
<p>
We could also give them full wraithform, which spectres traditionally have. 
</p>
<p>
Christopher: Sounds cool. I'd say give them a *lot* more sp than normal as it would be their health anand mana. Maybe someone could put it in a mod. (looks around pleadingly) 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./SoulWynd">SoulWynd</a>: Two thumbs up for this idea. Altho, I also think they shouldn't be able to wear any equipment or rather, only ragged/broken stuff and iten enchantments should work the oposite to them... a (-60, -60) {cursed} broken sword would turn into a +60 +60 normal sword while they're using it, with the bad effects turned into good effects... If they attempt to wear an item considered good, the effects become negative. 
</p>
